{"lemma":"صُحْبَةٍ","slug":"صُحْبَةٍ","root":"ص.ح.ب","root_slug":"ص-ح-ب","root_link":"/words/roots/ص-ح-ب","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":2,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":3},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n23773","n23780"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B5%D9%8F%D8%AD%D9%92%D8%A8%D9%8E%D8%A9%D9%8D"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"companions; collective of صَاحِب (ṣāḥib)"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of صَحِبَ (ṣaḥiba) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"companionship, fellowship"}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":["/sˤuħ.ba/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n23773","headword_ar":"صَحِبَهُ","root":"SHb","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SuHobapN","text_ar":"صُحْبَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, Msb, K, &c.) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SaHaAbapN","text_ar":"صَحَابَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SiHaAbapN","text_ar":"صِحَابَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He associated, kept company,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"consorted, with him;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, K;) ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he accompanied him;"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, his companion, associate, comrade, fellow, friend,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fellow-traveller:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(MA:) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SAHbhu","text_ar":"صاحبهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies the same. (TA. [See this latter verb below.]) ―         -b2-  [Hence] one says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SaHibaka A@ll~`hu","text_ar":"صَحِبَكَ ا@للّٰهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SaAHabaka","text_ar":"صَاحَبَكَ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (A, TA,) [inf. n. of the former (in the TA inadvertently said to be of the latter)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SiHaAbapN","text_ar":"صِحَابَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (said in the TA to be with kesr,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SaHaAbapN","text_ar":"صَحَابَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and, as will be shown by what follows,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SuHobapN","text_ar":"صُحْبَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"also,] (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"May God guard, keep, protect,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"defend, thee; may God be thy guardian, keeper,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.: (TA in explanation of the former:) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aHosana A@ll~`hu SaHaAbataka","text_ar":"اَحْسَنَ ا@للّٰهُ صَحَابَتَكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, and Ham p. 443) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SiHaAbataka","text_ar":"صِحَابَتَكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA) (tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"May God make the guarding,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of thee to be good"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. And (TA) [in like manner,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fulaAnFA","text_ar":"فُلَانًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ASHb","text_ar":"اصحب","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He guarded, kept,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"protected, such a one;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ASTHbhu","text_ar":"اصطحبهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he defended such a one;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"manaEahu","text_ar":"مَنَعَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (K, TA:) one says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"biSuHobapK","text_ar":"بِصُحْبَةٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aall~`hum~a A^aSoHibonaA","text_ar":"اَللّٰهُمَّ اَصْحِبْنَا","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waA^aqolibonaA bi*im~apK","text_ar":"وَاَقْلِبْنَا بِذِمَّةٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"O God, guard us with"},{"kind":"text","text":"thy"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"guarding"},{"kind":"text","text":"in our journey,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and make us to return with"},{"kind":"text","text":"thy"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"safeguard"},{"kind":"text","text":"to our country, or land, &c.; occurring in a trad.: (TA:) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"walaA humo min~aA yuSoHabuwna","text_ar":"وَلَا هُمْ مِنَّا يُصْحَبُونَ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (A, TA,) in the Kur [xxi. 44], (TA,) means (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Nor shall they"},{"kind":"text","text":"(i. e. the unbelievers, TA)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"be defended from us,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, TA,) as expl. by Zj; (TA;) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"preserved in safety:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A:) or, accord. to Katádeh,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"nor shall they be attended by good from us:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or, as some say, it is from the phrase"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SaHibaka A@ll~`hu","text_ar":"صَحِبَكَ ا@للّٰهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"meaning as expl. above. (TA.) ―         -b3-  See also 4, last sentence but one.       -A2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SaHaba","text_ar":"صَحَبَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SaHobN","text_ar":"صَحْبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TK,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He skinned"},{"kind":"text","text":"a slaughtered animal. (K.)"}],"source_refs":["S","A","K","MA","TA","TK"]},{"entry_id":"n23780","headword_ar":"صُحْبَةٌ","root":"SHb","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"an inf. n. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SaHibahu","text_ar":"صَحِبَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[q. v.]. (S, A, Msb, K, &c.) ―         -b2-  [As a simple subst.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Companionship."},{"kind":"text","text":"Hence,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lahu SuHobapN","text_ar":"لَهُ صُحْبَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", often occurring in biographies as meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He had companionship"},{"kind":"text","text":"with the Prophet; i. e. he was one of the Companions of the Prophet. And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xarajotu SuHobapa Alr~asuwli","text_ar":"خَرَجْتُ صُحْبَةَ الرَّسُولِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", frequently occurring in trads., meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I went forth in the companionship of the Apostle,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in company with the Apostle."},{"kind":"text","text":"Hence also] one says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hamalotu AlkitaAba","text_ar":"حَمَلْتُ الكِتَابَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SuHobatiY","text_ar":"صُحْبَتِى"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I carried the book with me"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (Msb.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SuHobapu Als~afiynapi","text_ar":"صُحْبَةُ السَّفِينَةِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The companionship of the ship"},{"kind":"text","text":"] is a post-classical phrase, denoting, by way of comparison, that which has no permanence. (Har p. 258.) ―         -b3-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SaAHibN","text_ar":"صَاحِبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", of which it is a quasipl. n."}],"source_refs":[]}]},"classical_definitions":null}